snippet.textDisplay: Maybe I'm just weird. But I actually really enjoy the food science part for this series. It's nice to know WHY I'm supposed to be doing certain things while cooking. When watching cooking vids, I get conflicting advice a lot (e.g. oil in pasta water). Not even professional chefs are immune to believing cooking myths. It's nice to hear the science behind it, to confidently know what works and what doesn't.
